A stronger, more versatile, and more stable platform for inside the waistband carry. Truly cant adjustable. Either strap can be moved up or down enabling you to properly cant the weapon. There are 3 different eyelet holes on each side, and 3 belt sizes on the soft loop. The holster is equally at home in the appendix position as well as strong side.The an offset configuration of the soft loops helps tuck the grip into your torso for maximum concealment ability while still allowing the gun to ride high enough to get a firm purchase on the draw. The holster allows for a very smooth drawstroke.

Additionally the holster can be run with the single strap/strut configuration and you have a simple, tuckable holster that is easy to don on or off.

title: For Sale/Trade:  SVT 40 Rifle - Excellent TULA 1942 w/Bayonet & accessories
postcontent:
I purchased this rifle at a 1991 Lakeland Gun Show. Back then I hardly ever missed a show and they used to sometimes have a preview late Friday afternoon before the show officially opened on Saturday morning. So I decided to attend that Friday, and way back in the far corner of the civic center was a dealer I hadn't seen before. He had two tables and was showing off some neat German WWII collectibles. However the thing that caught my attention immediately was a rack full of SVT 40's, and he must of had 10 of them. 

So I went right to that rack and began examining each one of them. They were all in very good or better overall shape. However while all looked very nice on the outside - most had some sort of issue with their bore's. Some were noticeably pitted, some frosted, and some dark, but the one that I ended up with was the pick of the litter, and the bore was in great shape with no darkening, pitting or frosting. Long story short - I negotiated a deal and bought the rifle on the spot. I had attended just about every gun show there was in central Florida back in the 80's & 90's and I never ran into anyone who had a rack full of SVT's before that Friday and haven't since. The SVT was pretty tough to find back then, and it's darn near impossible to expect to find one at a local Gun Show today.

Anyway this rifle is an arsenal refurb that was done right after the war. It's a 1942 Tula and the original numbering on the receiver matches the original stamping on the stock. The bolt and trigger group have electro penciled matching numbers (force matched during arsenal refurb process). The magazine and bayonet/scabbard are original and are in excellent condition, but numbers do not match the rifle. The accessories - leather mag pouch, RKA style ammo bandoleer and stripper clips are high quality reproductions that I purchased later to make an attractive display. There is also 100 rounds of Russian non corrosive 7.62 x 54 ammo included with the rifle. Finally there is an original Russian hat crest pin that completed my display.

I wanted to mention that the rifle does appear to have an import mark. However it's so small and lightly struck that I can't make it out, and my vision is excellent. It's so inconspicuous that it's only discernable  upon a very close and careful inspection - like magnifying glass.

I've had the rifle on display in my home for the last 20+ years, but I have never fired it. I have enjoyed showing it off over the years, but I'll be down sizing soon in preparation for an early retirement. So it's time to sell this to someone else who will appreciate what a true piece of WWII history this really is. 

My asking price for everything is $1400. Please do some research to avoid a low ball offer that I won't respond to. A rifle in this condition is easily worth my asking price with the bayonet and other accessories. This SVT is the nicest one I've come across and I doubt you could find any better at a similar price.

I apologize for the picture quality but it's difficult to do better with the equipment I have. Plus ARMSLIST only allows 3 pictures.  I would be happy to arrange for an inspection of the rifle for a serious buyer, but don't have time for window shoppers - sorry. Of course you must be a FL resident and at least 21 to purchase. I'm not looking for an out of state sale that requires shipping to an FFL at this time.
